{"id":14881045,"mediaExerciseId":"cfe24fe5-37b8-4e02-a060-a4f31655013e","exerciseName":"11","chapterName":"7","chapterTitle":"Interest Rates and Bond Valuation","groupId":612312,"groupTitle":"Critical Thinking Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":232,"solutions":[{"id":5976764,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"This task asks **why sometimes a company can face split ratings**.\n\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":30,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/01/2c743aeda3690203d414ee6d8fc43917/53f1e32028cf05b6192613480e54e2c8/lateximg_large.png","width":905},"regular":{"height":15,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/01/2c743aeda3690203d414ee6d8fc43917/53f1e32028cf05b6192613480e54e2c8/lateximg.png","width":453}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"Split rating happens when more agencies rating a specified company's debt provide different results. The same company for one rating agency may have a junk bond, for another rating agency have more than BBB rating. That is because the rating agencies used **different factors to determine the level of riskiness of the company**. Rating agencies do not use a prescribed form to calculate the firm's risk. **The agencies can insert their opinion in the results**, and it can cause split ratings.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":254,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/01/2c743aeda3690203d414ee6d8fc43917/2a5f9aec82b02effbefa2c267ad77f98/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":128,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/01/2c743aeda3690203d414ee6d8fc43917/2a5f9aec82b02effbefa2c267ad77f98/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"2f69cfbd-9389-49be-a4c1-2ed933c79c0f","editorVersion":